SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 1700
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR HENDERSON.
7208S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To repeal section 160.663, RSMo, and to enact in lieu thereof one new section relating to master
key boxes in schools.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Section 160.663, RSMo, is repealed and one new
2 section enacted in lieu thereof, to be known as section 160.663,
3 to read as follows:
1 160.663. 1. As used in this section, the following
2 terms mean:
3 (1) "Anti-intruder door lock", a mechanical or
4 electronic door-locking mechanism on an interior door that
5 is designed to keep an intruder from entering an interior
6 room that shall:
7 (a) Be capable of:
8 a. Locking from inside or outside the room;
9 b. Unlocking from outside the room with a key or other
10 approved means; and
11 (b) Control access to the room;
12 (2) "Exterior door or entryway", any location of
13 normal ingress and egress into or out of a school building;
14 (3) "Interior door", an egress door from a classroom,
15 office, or other occupied room that provides access to the
16 interior of a building;

SB 1700 2
17 (4) "Master key box", an exterior secure master key
18 box that meets the standards prescribed under Underwriters
19 Laboratories Standard 1037 for use by fire protection and
20 law enforcement.
21 2. Except as otherwise provided in this section, each
22 school district and charter school shall equip each interior
23 door with an anti-intruder door lock.
24 3. (1) A school district or charter school may equip
25 each school with one or more master key boxes to contain the
26 necessary keys and access tools for fire protection and law
27 enforcement agencies to gain access to exterior or interior
28 doors or entryways, including those equipped with an anti-
29 intruder door lock required under this section.
30 (2) On or before July 1, 2028, a school district or
31 charter school shall equip each school with at least one
32 master key box as provided in subsections 7 to 10 of this
33 section.
34 4. Notwithstanding any provision of this section to
35 the contrary, a school district or charter school shall not
36 be required to equip an interior door with an anti-intruder
37 door lock under this section unless the general assembly
38 specifically appropriates moneys to cover all costs related
39 to equipping such door or entryway with such lock.
40 5. (1) Each interior door installed after August 28,
41 2029, shall be equipped with the required anti-intruder door
42 lock.
43 (2) A school district or charter school may receive
44 donations of master key boxes and moneys for the purchase of
45 master key boxes.
46 (3) A school district or charter school may receive
47 donations of anti-intruder door locks and moneys for the
48 purchase of anti-intruder door locks.

SB 1700 3
49 6. Before or in conjunction with equipping interior
50 doors with anti-intruder door locks, each school district
51 and charter school shall develop and implement school
52 building access policies and practices that control access
53 to individual classrooms.
54 7. On or before July 1, 2028, each school district and
55 charter school shall install at each school at least one
56 master key box. Each master key box shall be installed at
57 an appropriate location to permit law enforcement officers
58 emergency access to each building and classroom or other
59 room on the school grounds. The school district or charter
60 school shall determine the precise location of each key box
61 after consultation with local law enforcement agencies of
62 the jurisdiction in which the school building is located.
63 Each school district or charter school shall provide each
64 local law enforcement agency of the jurisdiction in which
65 the school building is located with a key or access code
66 that permits access to the contents of the master key box.
67 8. Each master key box installed pursuant to
68 subsection 7 of this section shall contain:
69 (1) The keys and other access control devices
70 necessary to access each building and room on the entire
71 school grounds; and
72 (2) Accurate maps of the entire school grounds that
73 identify and label:
74 (a) Access points to each building's interior,
75 including rooms, doors, stairwells, and hallways. The maps
76 shall include the identifiers or names utilized by staff and
77 students to identify the rooms, doors, stairwells, and
78 hallways on the map;

SB 1700 4
79 (b) Locations of critical utilities, master key boxes,
80 automated external defibrillators, trauma kits, and other
81 emergency response aids; and
82 (c) Areas at or near each building, including parking
83 areas, athletic fields, surrounding roads, outbuildings, and
84 neighboring properties.
85 9. Notwithstanding any provision of chapter 610 to the
86 contrary, the contents of a master key box and the
87 information contained therein is not a public record and
88 shall not be made available for public examination.
89 10. An employee of a school district or charter school
90 is immune from civil liability for damages arising out of
91 the installation and use of master key boxes required by
92 this section unless the employee acted with gross negligence
93 or bad faith.
